    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Game for two players played on a special board; players have fifteen markers each, which they move around the board according to rolls of the dice. It evolved from other "tables" games in France ca. 1500.  While the boards are similar, tric-trac differs from backgammon in that racing is not such a significant part of the game. </Note_Text>
